
Overview of verb clap

The verb clap has 7 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (2) clap -- (put quickly or forcibly; "The judge clapped him in jail")
2. (1) clap -- (cause to strike the air in flight; "The big bird clapped its wings")
3. (1) applaud, clap, spat, acclaim -- (clap one's hands or shout after performances to indicate approval)
4. (1) clap, spat -- (clap one's hands together; "The children were clapping to the music")
5. clap -- (strike the air in flight; "the wings of the birds clapped loudly")
6. clap -- (strike with the flat of the hand; usually in a friendly way, as in encouragement or greeting)
7. clap -- (strike together so as to produce a sharp percussive noise; "clap two boards together")
